  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine the safety of transcranial direct current
      stimulation in aphasia therapy in acute and post-acute stroke.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      TDCS has been shown to have a positive effect on clinical outcome in both motor
      rehabilitation and aphasia treatment in chronic aphasic patients. In healthy subjects the
      method sped up reaction times in naming and language learning tasks. In TDCS a weak current
      is applied to the subjects head increasing excitatory activity which might lead to improved
      brain function.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
